## Bot Database Migrations (Direct mode)

Only used when BOT_DATA_MODE=direct (bot has its own database).
When BOT_DATA_MODE=api, the bot talks to the backend via REST â€” no direct DB access.

### Commands

```bash
cd src/telegram_bot

# Apply all pending migrations
alembic upgrade head

# Create a new migration after model changes
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "add_user_subscriptions"

# Check current version
alembic current
```

### Schema isolation

Bot uses `bot_app` PostgreSQL schema (configurable via DB_SCHEMA env var).
This allows sharing one database (e.g. Neon) with Django/FastAPI backends.
